# Feature Flags System

Feature Flags control the release behavior of LexMastery features.

They enable safe iteration.

---

# Product Vision

Feature Flags must:

- enable gradual rollout
- support A/B testing
- control AI feature exposure
- allow safe rollback
- support experimentation

---

# Architecture

FeatureFlagController

↓

FeatureFlagState

↓

FeatureFlagRepository

↓

Remote Config Service

---

# State Management

FeatureFlagState includes:

- activeFlags
- disabledFlags
- rolloutPercentages
- userOverrides

---

# Flag Types

- Boolean Flags
- Percentage Rollouts
- User-Specific Flags
- Environment Flags

---

# Use Cases

- Enable AI Tutor updates
- Gradually roll out quiz engine changes
- Test new onboarding flows
- Disable unstable features safely

---

# AI Integration

Feature flags can control:

- AI model versions
- prompt versions
- RAG activation levels

---

# Offline Behaviour

- cached flags used offline
- no remote sync offline

---

# API Contracts

GET /flags

POST /flags/update

GET /flags/user

---

# Analytics Events

flag_enabled

flag_disabled

flag_evaluated

flag_override_used

---

# UX Rules

- feature flags are invisible to users
- only affect system behavior

---

# Safety Rules

- never expose experimental features without flags
- always allow rollback

---

# Performance

- flag resolution <10ms target
- cached evaluation preferred

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Flag evaluation logic

Rollout system

Override handling

Integration Tests:

Feature toggle behavior

AI feature switching

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating features:

- always wrap experimental logic in flags
- always support rollback capability
- always separate stable vs experimental logic
- never hardcode experimental behavior